## Description

Whenever we're using `@vue/test-utils`, we require that `sync: false` is passed to `mount` and `shallowMount` because:

- In Karma, when this options is missing, [non-deterministic errors in unrelated tests will arise](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/issues/32213#note_231939709). :disappointed:
- `@vue/test-utils` [will be removing sync mode in the future](https://github.com/vuejs/vue-test-utils/issues/1137), so we'd rather not become dependent on it.

## Examples for this linter

Please keep in mind that in Karma [there's more boilerplate needed](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/issues/32213#note_231939709) which is out of scope for this linter.

```javascript
import { shallowMount, mount } from '@vue/test-utils';

// Bad :(
wrapper = shallowMount(FooComponent, { propsData });

// Good :)

wrapper = shallowMount(FooComponent, { propsData, sync: false });

// Bad :(
mount(FooComponent, { attachToDocument: true, sync: true });

// Good :)
mount(FooComponent, { attachToDocument: true, sync: false });
```
